            "secId": "s0005",
            "sentence": "1d ZnO nanostructures with long axes other than [0 0 0 1] (nanobelts due to rectangular cross section [5\u20137]) have been reported elsewhere and expand the possible applications exploiting polarization.",
            "startOffset": 10954,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 12856,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "Nanobelts grown on r-plane sapphire predominately grow tilted to the substrate in two directions (arrows in Fig. 1).",
            "startOffset": 12740,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 17918,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0020",
            "sentence": "We demonstrate the growth of non-polar 1d ZnO nanostructures, referred to as nanobelts, by MBE for the first time.",
            "startOffset": 17804,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 14237,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "Comparing XRD pole figures (Fig. SI1), confirms that only morphology changes with temperature and that the crystallographic orientation of the nanobelts doesn\u2019t change.",
            "startOffset": 14069,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 13016,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "The growth direction is determined by epitaxial relations of ZnO and the sapphire substrate and has the two-fold rotational symmetry of the sapphire substrate.",
            "startOffset": 12857,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 13344,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b0080": {
                    "endOffset": 13343,
                    "startOffset": 13339
                }
            },
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "At a lower growth temperature of 750 \u00b0C (Fig. 1(a)) the nanobelts are tapered, forming triangles similar to those previously grown on a-plane sapphire by PLD [16].",
            "startOffset": 13181,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 18416,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0020",
            "sentence": "This growth technique has possible applications in the growth of high quality heterointerfaces in 1d nanostructures where polarization mismatched interfaces may extend along the length of the nanostructure.",
            "startOffset": 18210,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 12717,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0010",
            "sentence": "TEM (aberration-corrected FEI Titan) was operated at 300 kV.",
            "startOffset": 12657,
            "title": "Experimental"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 12470,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0010",
            "sentence": "Nanobelts were characterized by helium ion microscope (HIM), X-ray diffraction (XRD), and high-resolution transmission electron microscope (HRTEM).",
            "startOffset": 12323,
            "title": "Experimental"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 13775,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b0085": {
                    "endOffset": 13722,
                    "startOffset": 13715
                },
                "b0090": {
                    "endOffset": 13722,
                    "startOffset": 13715
                },
                "b0095": {
                    "endOffset": 13722,
                    "startOffset": 13715
                }
            },
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "Tapering in quasi one-dimensional oxide nanostructures occurs due to side-wall growth [17\u201319] which is suppressed at increased growth temperature.",
            "startOffset": 13629,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 13628,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "At the maximum achievable temperature 890 \u00b0C (determined by the MBE), a significant fraction of the nanobelts (indicated by the red boxes in Fig. 1(c)) show almost no tapering.",
            "startOffset": 13452,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 18062,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0020",
            "sentence": "We may control the morphology of these nanostructures by changing their growth temperature, tapering being reduced with increasing temperature.",
            "startOffset": 17919,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 18209,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0020",
            "sentence": "At high temperature these nanostructures are roughly cuboidal and therefore have a pair of side faces very closely aligned to the (0 0 0 1) facet.",
            "startOffset": 18063,
            "title": "Conclusion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 10953,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "b0020": {
                    "endOffset": 10907,
                    "startOffset": 10902
                },
                "b0025": {
                    "endOffset": 10907,
                    "startOffset": 10902
                }
            },
            "secId": "s0005",
            "sentence": "ZnO nanowires grow along the polar [0 0 0 1] axis [4,5] (i.e. with the polar and long axes parallel).",
            "startOffset": 10852,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 12556,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0010",
            "sentence": "XRD (Rigaku SmartLab) was performed using Cu K\u03b1 emission with a wavelength of 1.54 \u00c5.",
            "startOffset": 12471,
            "title": "Experimental"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 13128,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "There are additionally a small number of 1d nanostructures which do not grow along one of these two directions.",
            "startOffset": 13017,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 15320,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "s0015",
            "sentence": "Tilting about a different axis to \u00b131\u00b0 brings one of the two dominant nanobelt growth directions parallel to the incident He-ion beam of the HIM as shown in Fig. 2(b, c).",
            "startOffset": 15150,
            "title": "Results and discussion"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 10663,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
